From Soup: 109 The range of [0.001, 0.050] for the noise amplitudes has been examined for the observation of spontaneous nucleation events. The amplitude does not change the intrinsic characteristics of the nucleation events except that a larger amplitude just shifts the metastable region of the disordered phase toward a smaller concentration of homopolymer .
