From Soup: 114 where and are two mobility coefficients, and and are the random noise terms, which are given by ( , ) = [ ( + 1, , ) − ( , , ) + ( , + 1, ) − ( , , )] in a lattice version, where and are random numbers uniformly distributed in the interval [−1, 1] and is the noise amplitude. Here we choose = = 0.004. A reasonably large amplitude of is needed to induce the spontaneous nucleation event. Starting from the disordered phase, this set of kinetic equations is solved numerically in 2D to obtain the time evolution of the system. In particular, the nucleation and growth of the ordered cylindrical domains are obtained from the numerical simulations.
